 \hspace{0.5cm}2^{n-1}(x^n + y^n) \\ \geq 2^{n-1} \cdot\max(x^n,y^n) \hspace{3cm}\text{---since 
} \\ = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 2^n \cdot \max(x^n,y^n) \hspace{3cm}\text{  ---arithmetic}\\ = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 2^n \cdot \max(x,y)^n \hspace{3cm}\text{  --- since 
}\\ = \frac{1}{2} \cdot (2 \cdot \max(x,y))^n \hspace{3cm}\text{  ---powers}\\ = \frac{1}{2} \cdot (\max(x,y) +\max(x,y))^n \hspace{1.5cm}\text{  ---arithmetic}\\ \geq \frac{1}{2} \cdot (x+y)^n \hspace{2.5cm}\text{---since 
 and non-negative powers preserve order}\\ = \frac{(x+y)^n}{2} \hspace{5cm}\text{---notation} 
